@Node "Introduction" "ExpName-E.guide/Introduction"
@Next "Copyright"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

Introduction
************

   This system shared library is able to decode the manufacturer  ID
and product ID of expansion boards. If the name of this board is known,
it is returned as string; otherwise you will receive a string
containing the decimal value of the ID, introduced by a @{b}#@{ub}.

   Though there are already a lot of names known, I still  rely  on
your help.  Please  send  the manufacturer name and id and the product
name and id of as much boards as possible! @{b}:-)@{ub}

   By the way: I have the feeling, some of you think that ListExp is
the main  part of this archive. This was not my intention! ListExp is
only a small demonstration tool. The  main  part  of  the  archive  is
the expname.library  itself. You can use it in your own programs to
decode as much board IDs as possible. Of course you can keep on using
ListExp only if you like! @{b}:-)@{ub}


@EndNode

