@Node "Usage" "ExpName-E.guide/Usage"
@Next "ListExp"
@Prev "Address"
@Toc "Main"

Usage
*****

   It is very simple to use the expname.library.

   If you want to get the name of a special expansion board, you can
pass the manufacturer ID and product ID directly to @{b}GetExpName()@{ub}. It is
mandatory to provide NULL as a pointer to the  ConfigDev  parameter if
you want to do so...

   If you want to get the name of all expansion boards or  of  a
special expansion  board,  you  have  to get a ConfigDev structure
first. Pass this structure to @{b}GetExpName()@{ub}, and voila... @{b}:-)@{ub}

   Additionally, @{b}expname.library@{ub} V2+ offers to query system parameters
like OS version, processor or memory size. To do so, you need to call
@{b}GetSysInfo()@{ub}, providing a buffer space and the ID code of the
information you want to receive (see include file).

   It is really that simple!


@EndNode

@Node "ListExp" "ExpName-E.guide/ListExp"
@Next "BoardsLib"
@Prev "Usage"
@Toc "Main"

ListExp
*******

   ListExp is a small tool (my first one written in C @{b};-)@{ub} ) which uses
the @{b}expname.library@{ub}. It lists all connected expansion boards, shows
their names (if possible), their address and their size.

   Try it out to see what @{b}expname.library@{ub} can do. If there are entries
which are introduced by a @{b}#@{ub} instead of a name, you should send ASAP a
description of the missing board to me...  @{b}:-)@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "BoardsLib" "ExpName-E.guide/BoardsLib"
@Next "Autodoc"
@Prev "ListExp"
@Toc "Main"

boards.library
**************

   Recently Torsten Bach released @{b}boards.library@{ub} in AmiNet.

   Except of the program code, Version 1.0 is a simple copy of the
@{b}expname.library@{ub}! Large parts of the documentation and include files are
copied, with the names replaced by Search&Replace.

   The program code is faulty. The library returns @{b}TRUE@{ub} if the
manufacturer or board is unknown, and @{b}FALSE@{ub} if both were known. This is
the opposite of what the Autodocs say.

   Additionally, his pragma file is useless.

   The @{b}boards.library@{ub} provided in this package, is a replacement of the
@{b}boards.library@{ub} of Torsten Bach. Internally, it uses @{b}expname.library@{ub},
ensuring full future compatibelity.


@EndNode

@Node "Autodoc" "ExpName-E.guide/Autodoc"
@Next "Bugs"
@Prev "BoardsLib"
@Toc "Main"

Autodoc
*******

@{i}NAME@{ui}
     GetExpName -- get name of expansion board

@{i}SYNOPSIS@{ui}
          Success = GetExpName(ManufName,ProdName,ConfigDev,Manufacturer,
            D0.l                  A0.l     A1.l      A2.l      D0.w
          		     Product)
          		       D1.b
          
          ULONG GetExpName(STRPTR,STRPTR,struct ConfigDev*,UWORD,UBYTE);

@{i}FUNCTION@{ui}
     Gets the name of the expansion and it's manufacturer.

@{i}INPUTS@{ui}
    @{b}ManufName@{ub}
          String to be filled with the manufacturer name. Must be at
          least 50 chars long (termination included).

    @{b}ProdName@{ub}
          String to be filled with the product name. Must be at least
          50 chars long (termination included).

    @{b}ConfigDev@{ub}
          Pointer to ConfigDev structure (from @{b}expansion.library@{ub}) or
          NULL.

    @{b}Manufacturer@{ub}
          ID of the board's manufacturer, if ConfigDev is NULL.

    @{b}Product@{ub}
          ID of the board's product number (depends on manufacturer),
          if ConfigDev is NULL.

@{i}RESULT@{ui}
    @{b}Success@{ub}
          True if both manufacturer and product are known. False if one
          of them was not known.

@{i}NOTE@{ui}
     If the manufacturer or the product is not known, the string will be
     filled with its number. I.e. it is NOT a real fault if this
     function fails; the strings can be used in any case...

     If you provide a ConfigDev structure, @{b}expname.library@{ub} may in some
     cases find out the name of a board even if it is not implemented.

     This call is guaranteed to preserve all registers except D0.

@{i}BUGS@{ui}
     There are by far not all existing boards implemented. Please send
     the manufacturer id and name and the products id and name of all
     unknown boards to me. My E-Mail: @{b}rkoerber@tfh.dssd.sub.org@{ub}.

@{i}SEE ALSO@{ui}
@{i}NAME@{ui}
     GetSysInfo -- get information about the system (V2)

@{i}SYNOPSIS@{ui}
          Buffer = GetSysInfo(Buffer,Type,Reserved)
           D0.l                A0.l  D0.l   D1.l
          
          STRPTR GetSysInfo(STRPTR,ULONG,ULONG);

@{i}FUNCTION@{ui}
     Gets information about the current system environment. This
     function is fully DraCo compatible!

@{i}INPUTS@{ui}
    @{b}Buffer@{ub}
          String to be filled with the information string. Must be at
          least 50 chars long (including termination).

    @{b}Type@{ub}
          Information type. These types are known in V2:
         @{b}EXPTYPE_SYSTEM@{ub}
               	 What system is used?
               ("Amiga","DraCo")

         @{b}EXPTYPE_CPU@{ub}
               	 What kind of CPU is available?
               (68000,68010,68020,...68060)

         @{b}EXPTYPE_FPU@{ub}
               	 What kind of FPU is available?
               (--,68881,68882,68040,68060)

         @{b}EXPTYPE_MMU@{ub}
               	 What kind of MMU is available?
               (--,68852,68030,68040,68060)

         @{b}EXPTYPE_OSVER@{ub}
               	 What OS version is used?
               (e.g. "V39.106")

         @{b}EXPTYPE_EXECVER@{ub}
               	 What exec version is used?
               (e.g. "V39.47")

         @{b}EXPTYPE_WBVER@{ub}
               	 What WorkBench version is used?
               (e.g. "V39.29", "--" if not available)

         @{b}EXPTYPE_ROMSIZE@{ub}
               	 Size of AmigaOS ROM
               (e.g. "512KB")

         @{b}EXPTYPE_CHIPSET@{ub}
               	 What Chipset is available?
               (e.g. "ECS","AGA","DraCo")

         @{b}EXPTYPE_GFXSYS@{ub}
               	 What Graphic Board System is used?
               (e.g. "CyberGraphX")

         @{b}EXPTYPE_CHIPRAM@{ub}
               	 Size of complete Chip RAM
               (e.g. "~2MB")

         @{b}EXPTYPE_FASTRAM@{ub}
               	 Size of complete Fast RAM
               (e.g. "12MB")

         @{b}EXPTYPE_RAM@{ub}
               	 Size of complete System RAM
               (e.g. "~14MB")

    @{b}Reserved@{ub}
          Reserved for future use, always provide 0 here!

@{i}RESULT@{ui}
    @{b}Buffer@{ub}
          Pointer to the provided buffer if everything went fine, NULL
          otherwise.

@{i}NOTE@{ui}
     This call is guaranteed to preserve all registers except D0.

@{i}BUGS@{ui}
@{i}SEE ALSO@{ui}

@EndNode

@Node "Bugs" "ExpName-E.guide/Bugs"
@Next "History"
@Prev "Autodoc"
@Toc "Main"

Known bugs
**********

   ExpName was written on an Amiga 4000/o3o/882/MMU, Kick 3.0, 14 MB
RAM, FastLane 1GB HD, MaestroPro, Toccata, BSC MultiIO, CyberVision 4MB.

@{i}THESE BUGS ARE CURRENTLY KNOWN@{ui}
          Some of the manufacturers have assigned one ID to two
          different boards. In this case, expname.library could result
          a board name that does not match to your hardware. Though it
          is not my fault, I'll try a bugfix very soon.

@{i}THESE ENFORCER HITS OR MUNGWALL HITS ARE KNOWN@{ui}
          None  @{b}:^)@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "History" "ExpName-E.guide/History"
@Next "Credits"
